  "body": "\r\n\r\n# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nCheckpoint sync backfill will by default download blocks until `MIN_EPOCHS_FOR_BLOCK_REQUESTS` has been reached. Users may want to backfill further than that, either to a previous known epoch where a node stopped to fill in a revived db (see https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/issues/13003) or all the way to genesis.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nAdd a flag like `--backfill-to-epoch` that will take the epoch number where backfill should stop. Backfill run until it hits the lower value of this flag or `MIN_EPOCHS_FOR_BLOCK_REQUESTS`.\r\n",
